# REST API Route Tester — Modern UI Plan

## Goals

- Deliver a **modern, product-style** admin tool: clear hierarchy, breathable spacing, subtle depth (shadows), and a **contemporary type stack** (system UI + monospace for JSON/routes).
- Use a **cohesive design token** layer (`#wprrt-app` CSS custom properties) for colors, radius, shadow, and typography so future tweaks are one place.
- Keep **WordPress admin usable** (contrast, focus states, no broken wp-admin layout) while **not** limiting the UI to “default gray boxes only.”
- **Responsive**: sidebar + two-column tab body stack cleanly under ~960px.
- **Polish**: primary/secondary/ghost button roles, elevated route dropdown, card-style response panel, refined tabs (pill / soft active state).
- Follow with **inline-style removal** in `src/tabs.js` (classes only) in a second pass for maintainability.

## Non-goals

- New JS framework, design tool handoff, or illustration pack.
- Full **dark mode** in this phase (tokens make it easier later).
- Changing REST/AJAX behavior.

## Architecture overview

- **Visual language**: slate/neutral surfaces + **indigo/blue accent** (`--wprrt-accent`), large radius (`10–12px`), soft shadow on cards and dropdown.
- **Typography**: `-apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto…` for UI; `ui-monospace / SF Mono` for code.
- **Structure**: unchanged DOM; styling is **`assets/style.css`** only for this phase.
- **Scoped tokens**: all variables live on `#wprrt-app` so they do not leak into global wp-admin.

## API compatibility notes

- No PHP/JS API changes for pure CSS refresh.
- Version bump `assets/style.css` via `rest-api-route-tester.php` `$version` when releasing.

## File-by-file change list

| Path | Changes |
|------|---------|
| `assets/style.css` | Token block; modern card/sidebar/tabs/form/response; responsive `@media`; `:focus-visible`. |
| `readme.txt` / `README.md` | Changelog line “Modern UI refresh” when shipping. |
| `src/tabs.js` | (Follow-up) Remove `style=` in favor of classes listed in this doc. |

## PR breakdown

1. **Modern CSS v1** — Tokens + component restyle (this deliverable).
2. **Markup cleanup** — Replace inline styles in `tabs.js` with classes matching CSS.

## Test plan

- Desktop 1280px + 782px: layout, tabs, dropdown, response scroll.
- Keyboard: focus rings visible on buttons and inputs.
- Long JSON: response panel scroll unchanged.

## Migration

- None. Cache-bust via enqueued version.

## Success criteria

- UI reads as **intentionally modern** (not default Arial gray).
- No functional regressions in testing flows.
